#. <section class="sutta" id="sn45.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn45.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 45"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 45"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Avijjāvagga"
msgstr "1. Ignorance"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn45.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Vibhaṅgasutta"
msgstr "8. Analysis"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.8:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn45.8:1.2"
msgid "“Ariyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ desessāmi vibhajissāmi."
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach and analyze for you the noble eightfold path."

msgctxt "sn45.8:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "sn45.8:1.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn45.8:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.8:2.1"
msgid "“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo?"
msgstr "“And what is the noble eightfold path?"

msgctxt "sn45.8:2.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"It is right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right "
"livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.8:3.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammādiṭṭhi?"
msgstr "And what is right view?"

msgctxt "sn45.8:3.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dukkhe ñāṇaṃ, dukkhasamudaye ñāṇaṃ, dukkhanirodhe ñāṇaṃ, "
"dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ñāṇaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Knowing about suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of "
"suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

msgctxt "sn45.8:3.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammādiṭṭhi."
msgstr "This is called right view."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.8:4.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāsaṅkappo?"
msgstr "And what is right thought?"

msgctxt "sn45.8:4.2"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, bhikkhave, nekkhammasaṅkappo, abyāpādasaṅkappo, avihiṃsāsaṅkappo—"
msgstr "It is the thought of renunciation, love, and kindness."

msgctxt "sn45.8:4.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāsaṅkappo."
msgstr "This is called right thought."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.8:5.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammāvācā?"
msgstr "And what is right speech?"

msgctxt "sn45.8:5.2"
msgid ""
"Yā kho, bhikkhave, musāvādā veramaṇī, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī, pharusāya "
"vācāya veramaṇī, samphappalāpā veramaṇī—"
msgstr "Avoiding speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical."

msgctxt "sn45.8:5.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāvācā."
msgstr "This is called right speech."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.8:6.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammākammanto?"
msgstr "And what is right action?"

msgctxt "sn45.8:6.2"
msgid ""
"Yā kho, bhikkhave, pāṇātipātā veramaṇī, adinnādānā veramaṇī, abrahmacariyā "
"veramaṇī—"
msgstr "Avoiding killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual activity."

msgctxt "sn45.8:6.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammākammanto."
msgstr "This is called right action."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.8:7.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāājīvo?"
msgstr "And what is right livelihood?"

msgctxt "sn45.8:7.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako micchāājīvaṃ pahāya sammāājīvena jīvitaṃ "
"kappeti—"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple gives up wrong livelihood and earns a living by "
"right livelihood."

msgctxt "sn45.8:7.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāājīvo."
msgstr "This is called right livelihood."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.8:8.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāvāyāmo?"
msgstr "And what is right effort?"

# MS punctuation.
msgctxt "sn45.8:8.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti "
"padahati, "
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts "
"the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise. "

msgctxt "sn45.8:8.3"
msgid ""
"uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya chandaṃ janeti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so "
"that bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen are given up."

msgctxt "sn45.8:8.4"
msgid "anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya chandaṃ janeti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so "
"that skillful qualities that have not arisen do arise."

msgctxt "sn45.8:8.5"
msgid ""
"uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya "
"bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ "
"paggaṇhāti padahati—"
msgstr ""
"They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so "
"that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, "
"mature, and are fulfilled by development."

msgctxt "sn45.8:8.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāvāyāmo."
msgstr "This is called right effort."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.8:9.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sammāsati?"
msgstr "And what is right mindfulness?"

msgctxt "sn45.8:9.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn45.8:9.3"
msgid ""
"vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid "
"of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn45.8:9.4"
msgid ""
"citte cittānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid "
"of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn45.8:9.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, "
"rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn45.8:9.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāsati."
msgstr "This is called right mindfulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.8:10.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sammāsamādhi?"
msgstr "And what is right immersion?"

msgctxt "sn45.8:10.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "sn45.8:10.3"
msgid ""
"Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter "
"and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of "
"immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without "
"placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "sn45.8:10.4"
msgid ""
"Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena "
"paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti "
"tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third "
"absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, "
"personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

msgctxt "sn45.8:10.5"
msgid ""
"Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ "
"atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati—"
msgstr ""
"Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they "
"enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with "
"pure equanimity and mindfulness."

msgctxt "sn45.8:10.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sammāsamādhī”ti."
msgstr "This is called right immersion.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn45.8:10.7"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
